reviews.review: Took me back to 1983, JJ did what he had to, to conclude this troubled trilogy. What The Last Jedi failed to do with exposition, TROS had to go at it at 100 miles per hour, but in the end gave an emotional strong finish! Best of the Sequel Trilogy by far.

A grand and fitting end to the story of the Skywalkers.  Let's face it, it's a big space opera (which I can enjoy because I don't suck all of the joy out with nitpicking ) and at the end of the day, this story, like most hero stories, has always been about the struggle between free will vs. destiny, and overcoming our demons, both the ones we choose and the ones thrust upon us.  And in that, this story succeeds well.
Excellent finale to the saga and a welcomed course correction after The Last Jedi. Abrams gave the fans the ending that they deserved. Loved it.

I liked the movie, the action parts, the battles, some dialogs; because at the end I didn't watch the nobbie (Rey) defeating the ultimate enemy (Palpatine), I could see every Jedi has ever been defeating him at last, after the masacre he planned (Order 66)

Really enjoyed this! It felt like a Star Wars movie unlike TLJ.

So many great moment and cried at a couple of points! Star Wars is back!

Great movie. As a Star Wars fan that has seen (and read) more than just the 9 main movies, I can't wait to learn more about all the new content this movie brought with it to be explored in the extended universe.
The movie was beautiful and had a great ending !
Totally awesome perfect ending to the saga

A beautiful send-off to the saga. The actors (with a special nod to Adam and Daisy) really gave it their whole heart and the story hit its major landings. JJ Abrams had a lot of hurdles to overcome and I think he and the team should feel good about what they've created here.

Mediocre at best, which still means it's better than TLJ by a country mile.  Acting was on par with the previous two movies and it had a good climactic action scene, but the plot was predictable and the twists obvious even with TLJ's efforts to derail all the characters' arcs.
